main event: A witness spotted a white, star-like, luminous, and bright object in the sky for approximately 2-3 minutes over Palos Verdes, California on July 19, 1965.
interesting points: The object had blinking blue, red, and green lights.
The object did not return at the time of the report.
The witness estimated the object was 15 to 20 miles away.
The witness was moving in a car at 55 mph when they observed the object.
The witness described the object as a circular object that became less distinct or faded out.
sighted object: a white, star-like, luminous, and bright object with blinking blue, red, and green lights
witnesses: two civilian males, telephone company employees and California police, ages 13 and 14 years respectively
